  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-02 21:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] I separated live HL directional telemetry from dead legacy state writers\n\n**Task:** Trace which process actually owns the stale HL state files, decide whether the live directional stack was missing writes or just being mislabeled, and harden the dashboard surface so P3 points at the real failure mode.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P3**.\n- The only live HL directional process is **`python3 -u hl_live_trader.py`** in the `hl-bot` screen.\n- `engine_state.json` is written only by **`hl_trading_engine.py`**.\n- `funding_arb_state.json` is written only by **`hl_funding_arb.py`**.\n- `momentum_state.json` is written by **`hl_momentum.py` / `momentum_strategy.py`**.\n- None of those legacy state-writer processes are running, so their stale JSON files are **not** evidence that the active directional bot is broken.\n- The live directional path is healthy from a telemetry standpoint: after my dashboard patch, `pillar3.hl_directional_owner = hl_live_trader.py`, `hl_directional_surface_summary = hl_live_trader telemetry fresh`, and `hl_trading.log` freshness is **0.6 minutes**.\n- The real blocker is still execution-wallet misalignment: `hl_live_trader.py` keeps warning that wallet **`0x51F2...3191`** has **$0.00** and is below the **$10** trading floor.\n- I patched `dashboard/update-dashboard.sh` so Pillar 3 now publishes state-file **owner**, **owner_running**, **ownership_status**, and live `hl_trading.log` freshness, then verified the dashboard refresh end-to-end.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p3-hl-state-ownership-2026-05-02.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The dashboard was collapsing two separate realities into one stale-state blob: retired strategy files and a live-but-wallet-blocked directional engine. That blurs the repair path. Once ownership is explicit, the strategy stack reads correctly: the JSON files are legacy debt, while the only live P3 issue is that the active trader is pointed at an empty exec wallet.\n\n**Decision:** Keep the new ownership-aware dashboard surface live. Do **not** treat `engine_state.json` staleness as a live directional outage anymore. For now, keep the legacy files visible but clearly tagged `legacy_inactive` so they stop hijacking diagnosis while still exposing cleanup debt.\n\n**Next:** On the next Pillar 3 pass, either add a dedicated `hl_live_trader` state file/heartbeat for direct cycle telemetry or prune legacy state files from the main execution surface if they are confirmed retired.\n\n## 2026-05-02 17:04 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] The first-trade warning is mostly old 19 UTC contamination, not a reason to ship a blanket cooldown\n\n**Task:** Re-test whether the `FIRST`-trade weakness in the PM smart-entry sample deserved a real new filter, and clear the remaining instrumentation gap if the sample was still dirty.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are aliv",
